Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.75,0:00:05.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of names...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.72,0:00:08.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are interesting stories\Nregarding how we were named.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.94,0:00:10.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regarding your names?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.33,0:00:13.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Shinichi-san, who passed away in Tokyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.86,0:00:18.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Said his real mother was forced to change his name\Nright before she submitted his registration of birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.90,0:00:18.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be1\shad0\bord0.8\b1\fscy100\fscx115\fad(900,0)\fncalibri\pos(105.727,203.349)}KU  DOU  SHIN  ICHI
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.62,0:00:20.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right before?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.94,0:00:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.82,0:00:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first, it was supposed to be written as the single\Ncharacter for "benevolence" and pronounced Hitoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.91,0:00:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur\shad0\bord1.3\b1\fscy190\fscx190\fad(360,0)\fncalibri\pos(106,54)}HITOSHI
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.95,0:00:27.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why was it changed?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.37,0:00:33.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall correctly, Shinichi-san said he heard it was changed\Nbecause our father thought Hitoshi would be too simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.96,0:00:38.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it's true that Hitoshi would have\Nonly a few strokes and would be simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.34,0:00:38.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.39,0:00:45.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}If Takako-san were a boy, the name would've had the characters\Nfor "ponder" and "season" with the reading of Kouki.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.76,0:00:44.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be1\shad0\bord0.8\b1\fscy110\fscx110\fad(340,350)\fncalibri\pos(311.371,180.188)}TAKA      KO
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.92,0:00:45.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be1\shad0\bord0.8\b1\fscy110\fscx110\fad(350,370)\fncalibri\pos(311.371,180.188)}KOU       KI
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.26,0:00:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}If Yoshiya-san were a girl, it would've been the kanji\Nfor "blessing" and "flower" pronounced Yuuka.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.56,0:00:50.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be1\shad0\bord0.8\b1\fscy110\fscx110\fad(420,460)\fncalibri\pos(82.569,176.337)}YOSHI      YA
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.10,0:00:52.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be1\shad0\bord0.8\b1\fscy110\fscx110\fad(420,460)\fncalibri\pos(82.569,176.337)}\hYUU       \h\hKA
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.63,0:00:57.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}If Tomoki-san were a girl, it would've been\N"know" and "spring" and read as Chiharu.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.02,0:00:55.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be1\shad0\bord0.8\b1\fscy110\fscx110\fad(420,330)\fncalibri\pos(310.5,177)}TOMO    AKI
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.61,0:00:58.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be1\shad0\bord0.8\b1\fscy110\fscx110\fad(420,600)\fncalibri\pos(310.5,177)}\h\h\h\h\hCHI     HARU\h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.44,0:01:02.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are all of those really names that\NPresident Tsunechika came up with?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.65,0:01:03.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.64,0:01:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}The ones who have passed away — Keiji-san,\NMiwako-san, and Saiki-san — all said so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.08,0:01:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be1\shad0\bord0.8\b1\fscy90\fscx90\fad(330,0)\fncalibri\move(219.375,127,224.625,119.5,6500,0)}KEI      JI
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.83,0:01:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be1\shad0\bord0.8\b1\fscy90\fscx90\fad(330,0)\fncalibri\move(70.875,233,79.125,225.5,5000,0)}MI  WA  KO
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.58,0:01:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be1\shad0\bord0.8\b1\fscy90\fscx90\fad(420,0)\fncalibri\move(221.25,216,225,209.5,5000,0)}SA      KI
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.66,0:01:12.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it looks like there's some sort of secret in their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.25,0:01:12.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.58,0:01:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.41,0:01:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rumor that the culprit is one of us adopted children...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.21,0:01:22.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And is using the demon dog with the intention\Nof rooting out the Inubushi bloodline?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.13,0:01:25.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't know about that yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.59,0:01:30.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we do know it's true that someone is\Nusing a trick to commit serial murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.51,0:01:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And a clue to the mechanism behind the demon dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.14,0:01:34.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has been picked up by us!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.18,0:01:37.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with that piece of cloth?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.77,0:01:41.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was on the ground next to where Tomoaki-san\Nhad been attacked by the demon dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.07,0:01:45.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no trace of it having been\Nburned, nor is there any smell of oil...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.82,0:01:48.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's no doubt it was used for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.86,0:01:51.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you picked up that sort of evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.41,0:01:53.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you hand it over to the police officer immediately?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.62,0:01:56.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takako-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.75,0:01:59.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were just now thinking of handing it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.25,0:02:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, Miyuki-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.25,0:02:04.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You left the kettle unattended on the stove!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.51,0:02:06.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.80,0:02:08.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I meant to go back immediately...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.76,0:02:12.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe we should go eat dinner right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.56,0:02:13.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.81,0:02:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And before we eat, tell us what the people\Nwho had stayed in the house were doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.11,0:02:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the deciding moment that determines your future...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.82,0:02:25.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You cannot lie to yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.12,0:02:27.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every mystery shall be solved!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.83,0:02:29.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The final chapter of the Demon Dog series!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.82,0:02:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.57,0:02:33.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.64,0:02:35.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.68,0:04:22.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The former head of the Inubushi family,\NTsunechika, died five years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.18,0:04:26.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And his surviving widow, the current head\NSatomi-san, had been confined to bed as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.65,0:04:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she were to pass away, the enormous inheritance\Nwould be divided amongst the eight adopted children.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.36,0:04:35.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But those adopted children began\Nto die by bizarre means, one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.62,0:04:40.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were these caused by the fiery demon dog's curse\Nthat's been tormenting the Inubushi family?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.75,0:04:45.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And finally, the demon dog appeared right in front of our very eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.00,0:04:49.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the identity of the monster that was engulfed\Nin flames and had been attacking people?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.46,0:04:53.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who on earth is controlling the demon dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.72,0:05:02.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.48,0:05:05.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you get this question?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.15,0:05:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it says the hint is "Try thinking about\Nit after putting on glasses," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.90,0:05:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you two doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.40,0:05:17.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're watching the midnight rerun of a quiz show.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.03,0:05:18.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.91,0:05:20.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not go to bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.24,0:05:21.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already past 1:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.87,0:05:23.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't the futons already laid out in the guest room?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.08,0:05:27.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, when we think about the demon dog being around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.42,0:05:29.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We get scared and can't sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.96,0:05:30.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.55,0:05:33.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, can you solve this code?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.72,0:05:33.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Thirty seconds left!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.63,0:05:35.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you solve it, we'll go to sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.92,0:05:37.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe Conan-kun can solve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.76,0:05:38.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's wearing glasses, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.30,0:05:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look here—the hint is glasses, or megane...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.06,0:05:45.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For this code, just turn all the "me" into "ne".
