Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.00,0:08:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like how Miyuki-san's former surname was Tamaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.04,0:08:21.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that if Takako-san were a boy, the name would've had the\Nkanji for "ponder" and "season" with the reading of Kouki.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.21,0:08:26.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if Yoshiya-san were a girl, it would've been the kanji\Nfor "blessing" and "flower", pronounced Yuuka.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.30,0:08:30.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Tomoaki-san were a girl, it would've been\N"know" and "spring" and read as Chiharu.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.81,0:08:31.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.89,0:08:34.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi-san, who passed away in Tokyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.48,0:08:38.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was supposed to have his name written as the single\Ncharacter for "benevolence" and pronounced Hitoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.19,0:08:45.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet it probably had something to do with the\Nprayer beads Satomi-san was grasping earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.20,0:08:47.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was grasping prayer beads?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.16,0:08:52.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They say she deliberately snuck out of her futon and grasped\Nonto the prayer beads that were inside the bureau.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.75,0:08:56.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, she cut the string in order\Nto allow just eight beads to remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.25,0:08:58.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beads...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.46,0:08:59.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eight...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.30,0:09:02.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that some kind of fortune-telling?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.21,0:09:05.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is there a type of fortune-telling that uses eight beads?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.22,0:09:08.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's not fortune-telling.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.35,0:09:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a folklore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.27,0:09:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A folklore?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.85,0:09:14.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have eight beads and a demon dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.52,0:09:17.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Add in the names of everyone in the Inubushi family...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.86,0:09:21.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's got to be Nansou Satomi Hakkenden!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.53,0:09:23.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hakkenden?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.24,0:09:25.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.78,0:09:28.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be1\1c&HAAE3E4&}\h\h\h\h\hhakken\N{\r}Is it a story about discovering something?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.70,0:09:30.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't know about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.45,0:09:33.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Written by the literary master of the Edo period, Takizawa Bakin...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.45,0:09:35.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a well-known long epic novel!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.42,0:09:39.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Satomi Yoshizane, having his castle\Nbesieged and assailed by the enemies...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.84,0:09:41.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Told his pet dog Yatsufusa:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.55,0:09:45.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"If you bring me back the head of their general,\NI'll let you marry my daughter Fusehime."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.55,0:09:51.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Surprisingly, Yatsufusa snuck into the enemy camp, decapitated\Ntheir general, and actually returned with his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.05,0:09:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fusehime thus said, "Even though it is a dog,\Nwe cannot go back on a promise as a ruler..."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.60,0:09:59.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And ended up secluding herself in the mountains with Yatsufusa.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.40,0:10:01.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how the prologue goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.23,0:10:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the heck is with that dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.40,0:10:06.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it cursed?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.40,0:10:08.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.99,0:10:13.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In fact, Yoshizane had become the castle lord by executing\Na treacherous retainer who had killed the previous lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.49,0:10:19.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the traitor's wife, Tamazusa, left this\Nfinal message as she was being beheaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.63,0:10:24.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Even as my body is destroyed, my soul\Nshall turn into a vengeful spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.38,0:10:28.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"And curse the Satomi clan through all eternity!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.09,0:10:32.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the curse Tamazusa muttered was placed on the dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.64,0:10:33.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.81,0:10:36.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though the curse put upon Yatsufusa was undone...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.52,0:10:39.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Fusehime's unceasing\Nefforts of reading buddhist scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.40,0:10:41.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.98,0:10:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened to the princess and the dog after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.61,0:10:49.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshizane ordered his retainers to kill\Nthe cursed dog and rescue the princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.53,0:10:53.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Fusehime shielded Yatsufusa\Nfrom the attack and died as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.53,0:10:55.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.66,0:10:59.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eight of the prayer beads the princess had\Non her were scattered to the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.62,0:11:05.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the odysseys of the eight swordsmen with names having the\Nkanji for "dog" and blessed by the beads in various regions...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.99,0:11:09.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Was described in Nansou Satomi Eight Dog Chronicles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.64,0:11:09.68,titlex2,,0,0,0,,{\fscx115\fad(460,0)\pos(192.198,197.271)}EIGHT DOG CHRONICLES
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.64,0:11:09.68,titlex2,,0,0,0,,{\fscx70\fscy70\fad(460,0)\b0\pos(188.352,166.182)}Nansou Satomi Hakkenden
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.34,0:11:14.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what does that have to do with the names?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.39,0:11:20.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Engraved in each of the eight prayer beads\Nwere one of these characters, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.64,0:11:25.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Benevolence, justice, courtesy, wisdom,\Nloyalty, faith, filial piety, and respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.90,0:11:30.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The characters for the eight virtues!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.07,0:11:35.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the Inubushi family members don't\Nhave those kanji in their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.83,0:11:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although Shinichi-san was named Hitoshi\Nwith the meaning of "benevolence"...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.33,0:11:41.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was changed because they say it was too simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.37,0:11:44.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't because it was too simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.08,0:11:46.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rather, it was avoided since it was too obvious!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.26,0:11:50.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be1\shad0\bord1.2\b1\fscy145\fscx145\fad(460,210)\fncalibri\pos(286.496,72.143)}SHIN        ICHI
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.88,0:11:52.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you take the {\t(720,721,\1c&H80FFFA&)}{\t(4090,4091,\1c&HFFFFFF&)}man {\r}radical from Shin, and add\Nthe two upper horizontal lines from Ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.97,0:11:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\shad0\blur5\1c&HFCFBFD&\3c&HFCFBFD&\bord6\pos(293.998,73.977)}{\t(0,170,\bord1)\shad0\b1\fscy145\fscx145\fncalibri\pos(293.368,46.378)}{\t(171,290,\1c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&\blur0)}JIN
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.97,0:11:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\shad0\blur5\1c&HFCFBFD&\3c&HFCFBFD&\bord6\pos(291.068,241.355)}{\t(0,170,\bord1)\shad0\b1\fscy145\fscx145\fncalibri\pos(293.368,46.378)}{\t(171,290,\1c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&\blur0)}BENEVOLENCE
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.01,0:11:54.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll get the Jin character, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.51,0:11:56.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.47,0:11:57.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.51,0:12:01.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of directly using the kanji, they were\Nsplit into parts and placed into the names!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.35,0:12:06.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takako-san would have the top part of the\N"ponder" kanji put together with the Ko...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.77,0:12:08.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To form Kou meaning filial piety.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.61,0:12:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she had been a boy, the name Kouki\Nwould have the same parts too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.57,0:12:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.57,0:12:18.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshiya-san has the show radical and the\Nlast swoosh of the Ya character to form...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.66,0:12:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rei, or courtesy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.04,0:12:23.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for Tomoaki-san, by removing the\Nbottom part of the Aki character...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.92,0:12:26.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You get Chi like in Akechi Kogorou!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.46,0:12:28.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murdered Keiji-san would be Chuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.25,0:12:31.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miwako-san would be Gi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.47,0:12:32.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saki-san would be Shin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.51,0:12:36.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And President Tsunechika would\Nbecome the Tei character, so to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.01,0:12:39.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the reason Satomi-san is called princess is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.76,0:12:42.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the woman radical from the bottom\Nof Sa in addition to the second kanji...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.77,0:12:44.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will form the kanji for princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.02,0:12:46.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.27,0:12:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet President Tsunechika must have\Nreally loved the Eight Dog Chronicles...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.90,0:12:53.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he inserted the kanji on the\Nbeads into the names of his children!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.65,0:12:55.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what about Miyuki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.16,0:12:57.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What virtue kanji is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.62,0:13:02.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I recall that before she became an adopted child, her name was\NMiyuki but written with just the one kanji from happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.21,0:13:05.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, the culprit is ascertained.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.51,0:13:10.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be1\shad0\bord1.2\b1\fscy245\fscx245\fad(460,0)\fncalibri\pos(203.502,264.215)}TAMA         KI          MIYUKI
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.26,0:13:17.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be1\shad0\bord1.2\b1\fscy245\fscx245\fad(100,0)\fncalibri\pos(196.725,258.799)}TAMA       ZUSA
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.33,0:13:08.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Combining her former surname of Tamaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.08,0:13:11.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the Miyuki character with one of the top lines removed...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.88,0:13:14.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We get Tamazusa.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.09,0:13:16.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the name of the evil spirit that cursed the Satomi clan...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.13,0:13:17.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the Eight Dog Chronicles!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.14,0:13:20.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.76,0:13:26.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying Miyuki-san is the serial murderer who's been\Ncontrolling the demon dog and killing the Inubushi people?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.29,0:13:38.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying Miyuki-san is the serial murderer who's been\Ncontrolling the demon dog and killing the Inubushi people?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.68,0:13:39.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.75,0:13:44.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roleplaying as Tamazusa, each time she killed the adopted\Nchildren representing the eight dog swordsmen...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.10,0:13:47.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She would leave a sphere behind as a symbol at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.46,0:13:49.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's just nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.18,0:13:50.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miyuki-san is a good person!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.48,0:13:55.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just because she's a good person\Ndoesn't mean she can't be the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.13,0:13:57.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.63,0:13:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.57,0:14:00.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji, say it isn't true!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.63,0:14:02.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miyuki-san isn't the culprit, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.18,0:14:04.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.43,0:14:05.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.06,0:14:09.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun isn't here either!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.52,0:14:10.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.98,0:14:11.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.48,0:14:15.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did Miyuki-san mention she was going to do something tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.11,0:14:19.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She did say she was going to stay up all night\Nand watch over Satomi-san in her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.12,0:14:22.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that she wouldn't sneak out of her futon again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.41,0:14:25.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.16,0:14:28.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miyuki-san has disappeared, you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.96,0:14:32.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I reckoned that overnight care taking was tough...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.79,0:14:36.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I entered this room to offer to take turns,\Nbut instead I found this letter left here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.76,0:14:37.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.88,0:14:44.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will atone for all the crimes I committed at\Nthe cabin where I raised the demon dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.35,0:14:45.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miyuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.97,0:14:47.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.81,0:14:48.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.14,0:14:50.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miyuki-san is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.81,0:14:51.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.36,0:14:53.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did she do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.66,0:15:07.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That scooter...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.37,0:15:10.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that Miyuki-san's?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.29,0:15:10.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.54,0:15:14.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me the gasoline's leaking out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.71,0:15:15.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.96,0:15:17.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's going to check things out?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.42,0:15:19.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want to!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.43,0:15:21.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall also decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.30,0:15:24.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Detective, why don't you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.85,0:15:27.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Heiji were here, I bet he'd be the one charging in first...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.10,0:15:29.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.18,0:15:31.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder where Conan-kun ran off to as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.15,0:15:38.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Demon dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.74,0:15:39.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.40,0:15:42.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's headed to the cabin!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.78,0:15:43.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.20,0:15:45.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it sets off the gasoline, the cabin will...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.87,0:15:50.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.00,0:15:51.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.87,0:15:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.10,0:16:06.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.76,0:16:07.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.60,0:16:09.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.64,0:16:10.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not burning...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.77,0:16:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it's just emitting a red light?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.27,0:16:14.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.06,0:16:17.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ragged cloth around the dog's body...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.69,0:16:19.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's imitation fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.19,0:16:21.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.95,0:16:22.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Imitation fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.41,0:16:27.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}It was also on the set of that quiz\Nshow you were watching too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.08,0:16:27.03,titlex2,,0,0,0,,{\fscx140\fscy140\fad(290,0)\pos(195.437,143.544)}IMITATION FIRE
