Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.95,0:16:33.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Blowing wind over shiny pieces of cloth with red LED\Nlights affixed to them creates the fake fire effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.00,0:16:36.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the same for that dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.88,0:16:40.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was covered in cloth so that the cloth fluttered when it ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.51,0:16:46.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Red lights were set up under the cloth, and that's\Nwhy it really looked like it was a fiery demon dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.97,0:16:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the lights were turned off via remote control, the dog\Nwould be able to disappear instantly from our view.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.52,0:16:55.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what about these flaming footprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.06,0:16:56.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a close look.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.60,0:17:00.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're just disposable lighters that had the gas\Noutlet manipulated so that it would stay lit...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.44,0:17:02.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And strung on a piano wire, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.99,0:17:04.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.24,0:17:08.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The odor I smelled when I fell was the gas from the lighters?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.99,0:17:10.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.03,0:17:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gas is originally odorless and therefore dangerous...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.45,0:17:14.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they added a scent similar to that of rotten onions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.83,0:17:18.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time you guys were chased by that\Ndemon dog at the Inubushi house...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.29,0:17:23.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you fell, you forced the lighter into the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.97,0:17:26.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why it was the only place where\Nthe flaming footprints were absent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.59,0:17:30.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, no matter how much the gas comes out, if it's not on fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.60,0:17:35.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The spark for the flames was this charcoal enclosed\Nin wire mesh that was attached to the dog's tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.56,0:17:40.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the dog passed over the lighters while\Nwearing this, they'd quickly catch on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.44,0:17:43.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I bet the dog had not been attacking people...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.90,0:17:48.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But rather, it was chasing the scent of the gas the\Nculprit laid on the ground, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.07,0:17:52.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, after we were attacked in the backyard at the house...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.99,0:17:55.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There weren't any lighters on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.71,0:17:59.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The dog was trained to return home while\Nbiting the end of the piano line.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.29,0:18:05.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the demon dog disappeared, the flames were hopping\Naround with a crackling and popping sound because of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.92,0:18:09.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the dog was dragging the piano wire with\Nall those lighters attached while it was running...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.64,0:18:14.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lighters would have hit the rough surface\Nof the ground, causing said effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.68,0:18:20.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when Tomoaki-san was attacked by the dog, there\Nwere flames on his arm and he suffered burns, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.73,0:18:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course he'd suffer burns.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.94,0:18:27.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because you purposely set yourself on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.41,0:18:32.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to make people think the demon dog was actually burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.08,0:18:36.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Tomoaki-san is the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.04,0:18:40.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, weren't you attacked by the demon dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.96,0:18:46.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The pet dog was simply trained to\Njump on his master — you — in joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.63,0:18:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we were investigating the cabin, he took out the piano wire\Nwith the lighters attached from his bag and laid them out...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.22,0:18:57.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he used a dog whistle to call the dog out\Nfrom the real doghouse somewhere near here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.73,0:19:01.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when he and the dog came together and\Nfell in the blind spot of the embankment...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.86,0:19:06.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He turned off the lights on the dog, had it\Nreturn home, and set fire to his own arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.82,0:19:11.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the onion meant to misrepresent the odor that\NKazuha smelled was placed at that time as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.87,0:19:17.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Miyuki-san's letter saying she'd\Natone for the crimes here was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.95,0:19:20.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was written by Tomoaki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.12,0:19:23.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to set Miyuki-san up as the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.29,0:19:26.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, where is Miyuki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.01,0:19:31.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was put to sleep inside that cabin,\Nso we moved her to another location.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.68,0:19:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because Miyuki-san was looking for\Nsomething here along with Tomoaki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.72,0:19:43.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet she was asked to help look for Satomi-san's medicine that\Nyou supposedly dropped when you were attacked by the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.15,0:19:46.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were you watching us?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.65,0:19:47.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.86,0:19:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because we've been trailing you from\Nthe house, we immediately realized it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.90,0:19:54.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason you drugged Miyuki-san\Nto sleep and took her to this cabin...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.12,0:20:00.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was to make it look like she committed\Nsuicide by fire along with the demon dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.14,0:20:00.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.67,0:20:05.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No use trying to play dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.13,0:20:08.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dogs never forget their masters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.71,0:20:13.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the reason Hachi barks at you is\Nprobably because you smell like this dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.80,0:20:16.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, Satomi-san already knows everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.35,0:20:22.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since you lied about your alibi of\Nwatching over her the entire time...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.73,0:20:24.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course your lies would be exposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.02,0:20:30.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason why Satomi-san was grading the eight prayer beads,\Nwith the fourth one from the top being a black heavenly bead...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.99,0:20:36.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Was because among Jin, Gi, Re, Chi,\NChuu, Shin, Kou, Tei, the fourth was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.16,0:20:39.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Chi, meaning you were the culprit with this name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.08,0:20:42.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as for the reason Satomi-san\Nhad tears rolling down her cheek...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.58,0:20:47.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was because she hoped you'd be the first to\Ndiscover the beads and turn yourself in, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.29,0:20:51.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All in the order to not let your crimes accumulate any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.05,0:20:58.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the Inubushi Manor resembling a castle so much...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.89,0:21:01.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want to let go of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.31,0:21:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since the inheritance tax was skyhigh...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.02,0:21:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had to do it in order to increase my inheritance share.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.53,0:21:20.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mama Satomi, whom I felt even closer to than my\Nown mother, had been keeping her memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.58,0:21:22.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this very castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.33,0:21:27.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this very castle is the last thing I want to let go...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.17,0:22:54.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the credit is all mine again!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.34,0:22:58.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He coughed up everything as he was\Ncrying in the interrogation room.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.59,0:23:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he killed those four who didn't\Nhelp out with maintaining the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.26,0:23:08.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, didn't Shinichi-san give up his share of the inheritance?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.77,0:23:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That wasn't because of the inheritance...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.60,0:23:13.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in order to make it seem like a crime\Ncaused by Tamazusa's curse, he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.52,0:23:20.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he really thinks that Miyuki-san was Tamazusa's\Nreincarnation who had come to destroy this castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.24,0:23:25.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the time Satomi-san collapsed was in the middle\Nof her wild vegetable gathering with Miyuki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.54,0:23:28.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.87,0:23:30.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall protect it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.92,0:23:31.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.21,0:23:33.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miyuki-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.84,0:23:35.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I am, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.59,0:23:38.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A princess of this castle, just like Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.71,0:23:41.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, unlike Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.34,0:23:43.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're quite an unrefined princess!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.85,0:23:45.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please don't say that!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.68,0:23:47.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.31,0:23:49.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, they're the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.27,0:23:51.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you combine the fushi kanji from Inubushi...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.85,0:23:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the hime kanji from her name...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.86,0:23:58.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both of them would be Fusehime.
